<FIRST>r i AMBritain-Amnesty     06-14 0189</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM Britain-Amnesty,0193</SECOND>
<HEAD>Amnesty says 85 U.N. members violate human rights charter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Amnesty </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> said Wednesday that 85 of the 159 members of the <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nations </ORGANIZATION> violate the organization's <ORGANIZATION> Universal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Declaration </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Human </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Rights </ORGANIZATION> In a report covering the first four months of 1988, London-based <ORGANIZATION> Amnesty </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> said it had identified 3,352 individual cases of people jailed for the non-violent excercise of their rights as defined by the <ORGANIZATION> U.N. </ORGANIZATION> document. The declaration, adopted by the <ORGANIZATION> U.N. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> General </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Assembly </ORGANIZATION> in 1948, calls for civil, political, economic, social, and cultural rights for all people. <ORGANIZATION> Amnesty </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> reported it had issued 115 appeals since Jan. 1 to 45 countries involving more than 450 prisoners who the human rights organization said it considers at risk of violations of their rights including torture and death. The report said <ORGANIZATION> Amnesty </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> sent 18 missions to 15 countries from January-April and issued 98 documents on human rights violations. `` None of these reports or initiatives should have been necessary,'' it said. `` In the 40th anniversary of the <ORGANIZATION> Universal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Declaration </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Human </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Rights </ORGANIZATION>, such abuses should have become only a ghost from the past.''
