<DATELINE>KNOXVILLE, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> Joy </PERSON> <PERSON> Baker </PERSON>, wife of White House Chief of Staff <PERSON> Howard </PERSON> <PERSON> Baker </PERSON>, was resting in a <LOCATION> Knoxville </LOCATION> hospital where she was being treated for a chronic back problem, a hospital spokeswoman said. Mrs. <PERSON> Baker </PERSON> was admitted to <ORGANIZATION> St. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mary </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Medical </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Center </ORGANIZATION> on Thursday and was in satisfactory condition Monday, said hopital spokeswoman <PERSON> Janice </PERSON> <PERSON> Webster </PERSON>. Ms. <PERSON> Webster </PERSON> said <PERSON> Baker </PERSON> visited his wife at least once Monday. Also Monday, <PERSON> Baker </PERSON>'s stepmother, <PERSON> Irene </PERSON> <PERSON> Baker </PERSON>, was being treated at <LOCATION> Baptist </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hospital </LOCATION> in <LOCATION> Knoxville </LOCATION>. Hospital officials said <PERSON> Irene </PERSON> <PERSON> Baker </PERSON> was admitted Sunday with stomach pains and was in fair condition Monday.
