<HEAD>Daughter of Sonny and Cher Likes to Keep a Low Profile</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Chastity <PERSON> Bono </PERSON>, the 19-year-old daughter of <PERSON> Sonny </PERSON> <PERSON> Bono </PERSON> and <PERSON> Cher </PERSON>, says she's a casual `` jeans and T-shirt'' kind of person, unlike her fashion-plate mother. `` I was never into that from the start,'' Miss <PERSON> Bono </PERSON> says of her mother's taste for flashy, provocative clothes. `` Chas,'' as she likes to be called, says in July's <PERSON> McCall </PERSON>'s magazine that living with <PERSON> Cher </PERSON> is `` never just a quiet day at home with nobody around. In contrast, she says, `` One thing I've always liked about being at Dad's: It's always been really calm and normal. That serenity is one thing he gave me that's really important.'' The years after her parents divorced were difficult, Miss <PERSON> Bono </PERSON> said. `` My parents were n't around a lot,'' she said. `` The divorce hit when I was 3, and I would go back and forth between my parents' houses _ crying for each one when I was with the other. She said it took her awhile to adjust to the many companions of both parents. `` It was difficult because I'd get attached to someone and they'd leave,'' she said. `` But it did n't bother me after a while because it was just their lives, not my life. And it is n't like these people are coming in and trying to be my new mom and dad; they're just friends.''
