> was responsible for its repayment. <PERSON> Mecham </PERSON> was charged with six felony counts of perjury, willful concealment and filing false documents and faced up to 22 years in prison if convicted. <PERSON> Willard </PERSON> <PERSON> Mecham </PERSON>, who was his brother's 1986 campaign treasurer, faced three similar counts and up to 9 -LCB- years in prison if convicted. <PERSON> Mecham </PERSON>, a Republican, took office in January 1987 and was removed April 4 when the state <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> convicted him of two unrelated charges.
