<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> Carl </PERSON> <PERSON> C. </PERSON> <PERSON> Icahn </PERSON> says he has put $ 310.2 million into an escrow account to be divided among <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> shareholders if he fails to come up with financing for his $ 60-per-share offer to buy the company. At its <LOCATION> White </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Plains </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> N.Y. </LOCATION>, headquarters, the nation's third-largest oil company reacted skeptically to the action Monday by its biggest shareholder, saying <PERSON> Icahn </PERSON> had `` been caught red-handed giving the <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION> shareholder false and misleading information. `` Given the number of strings and conditions that remain attached to this money, it does n't matter to the <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION> shareholder what account <PERSON> Icahn </PERSON> puts it in,'' <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION> stated. `` He can move it from one pocket to another as much as he wants _ we are still convinced it will never get to <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION> shareholders.'' <PERSON> Icahn </PERSON> also said he had sent a signed `` bare bones'' $ 60 a share merger agreement to the company. `` If <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION> executes the merger agreement, we will terminate our proxy contest and withdraw our slate of nominees,'' the statement said, referring to <PERSON> Icahn </PERSON>'s attempt to elect himself and four colleagues to <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION>'s board of directors. <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION> has said repeatedly it was not interested in <PERSON> Icahn </PERSON>'s advances <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION>'s stock slid $ 1.37 -LCB- to $ 50.50 a share Monday in consolidated nationwide trading of <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> Exchange-listed issues. It has remained in the $ 50-per-share range since <PERSON> Icahn </PE