<HEAD>Mazda Combining Two U.S. Sales Companies Into One, Laying Off 75
Workers</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JANET BRAUNSTEIN</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Auto Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION>'s <ORGANIZATION> Mazda </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motor </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> will combine its two <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> sales and importing companies into one July 1, eliminating 70 jobs at one of the companies' headquarters in <LOCATION> Jacksonville </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Fla. </LOCATION>. <ORGANIZATION> Mazda </ORGANIZATION> is combining <ORGANIZATION> Mazda </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motors </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> America </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Central </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Mazda </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motors </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> America </LOCATION> <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> into <ORGANIZATION> Mazda </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motor </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> America </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>. About 20 of the 330 workers at the <LOCATION> Mazda </LOCATION> <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> headquarters will be laid off by the end of June, <PERSON> Yoshinori </PERSON> <PERSON> Taura </PERSON>, president of the new <LOCATION> Irvine </LOCATION>, Calif.-based company, said In the next three to six months, 45 to 50 other <LOCATION> Jacksonville </LOCATION> workers will be laid off. But those workers were given bonuses to stay through the transition and all 70 will be assisted in finding jobs, <PERSON> Taura </PERSON> said. `` I feel very sorry for those workers. It is not our desire to have to ask them to leave. We will help them,'' <PERSON> Taura </PERSON> said, adding that the consolidation would improve <ORGANIZATION> Mazda </ORGANIZATION>'s efficiency in the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> market. `` We believe the improved efficiency and services that will result from this reorganization of our <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> marketing activity will be reflected in an enriched product line, one which more closely reflects the needs and desires of our customers here,'' <PERSON> Taura </PERSON> said. The use of two sales companies by a foreign company in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> was unique to <ORGANIZATION> Mazda </ORGANIZATION>. <ORGANIZATION> Mazda </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Central </ORGANIZATION>, which included 31 states, and <LOCATION> Mazda </LOCATION> <LOCATION> East </LOCATION>, which included 18, were formed 11 years ago, when <ORGANIZATION> Mazda </ORGANIZATION> was suffering financially. A company that imported into <LOCATION> Hawaii </LOCATION> also will be folded into the new company. Each company was half-owned by <ORGANIZATION> Mazda </ORGANIZATION>. The other partner in Mazda Central was <PERSON> C. </PERSON> <PERSON> Itoh </PERSON> and Co.. <ORGANIZATION> Ltd. </ORGANIZATION>, a big Japanese trading company, which will own 20 percent of <ORGANIZATION> Mazda </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motor </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> America </ORGANIZATION> The <LOCATION> Mazda </LOCATION> <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> partner was <ORGANIZATION> Sumitomo </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Mazda </ORGANIZATION>'s banker, which will own 30 percent of the new company. <PERSON> Taura </PERSON> was president of <ORGANIZATION> Mazda </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Central </ORGANIZATION>, which will keep all its workers. About 15 Americans and 10 Japanese Mazda East workers will be transferred from <LOCATION> Jacksonville </LOCATION> to <LOCATION> Irvine </LOCATION>, he said. Taura will report to <PERSON> Keiji </PERSON> <PERSON> Asano </PERSON>, a senior managing director of the parent company, who was named chairman of <ORGANIZATION> Mazda </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motor </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> America </ORGANIZATION> and who is based in <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION>. <ORGANIZATION> Mazda </ORGANIZATION> has three other companies in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>. The newly formed <ORGANIZATION> Mazda </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Research </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Development </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> North </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> America </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> will handle product testing and evaluation and development of new materials and other research. <PERSON> Hiroshi </PERSON> <PERSON> Moriyoshi </PERSON> was named president of that company, which is based in <LOCATION> Irvine </LOCATION>, where it has a new $ 23 million design center. <ORGANIZATION> MRA </ORGANIZATION> also has operations in <PERSON> Ann </PERSON> <PERSON> Arbor </PERSON> and <LOCATION> Flat </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Rock </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Mich. </LOCATION>, and in <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> D.C </LOCATION>. It is a wholly-owned subsidiary of <ORGANIZATION> Mazda </ORGANIZATION> -LRB- <ORGANIZATION> North </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> America </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> -RRB- </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>. <ORGANIZATION> Mazda </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motor </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Manufacturing </ORGANIZATION> -LRB- <LOCATION> USA </LOCATION> -RRB- <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> builds cars at <ORGANIZATION> Mazda </ORGANIZATION>'s new assembly plant in <LOCATION> Flat </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Rock </LOCATION> The plant began production in September, building the Ford Probe and the <ORGANIZATION> Mazda </ORGANIZATION> MX-6, both sporty coupes. The Flat Rock plant also will begin building the Mazda 626 sedan in 1989. <ORGANIZATION> Mazda </ORGANIZATION> -LRB- <ORGANIZATION> North </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> America </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> -RRB- </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, also based in <LOCATION> Irvine </LOCATION>, will ship cars from the Flat Rock plant, supply parts and accessories to the plant and to <ORGANIZATION> Mazda </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motor </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> America </ORGANIZATION> and provide other parent-company support.
