<SECOND>BC-Japan-Tax Reform,0568</SECOND>
<HEAD>Ruling Party Outlined Proposal For Tax Reform</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By TETSUO JIMBO</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The ruling <ORGANIZATION> Liberal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Democratic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> approved a blueprint for sweeping reform of the national tax system on Tuesday, and pegged a controversial consumer sales tax at 3 percent, party officials said. The <ORGANIZATION> LDP </ORGANIZATION>'s <ORGANIZATION> Tax </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> System </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Research </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Council </ORGANIZATION> completed the final plan that could pave the way for the first major overhaul of <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION>'s postwar tax system The <ORGANIZATION> LDP </ORGANIZATION> draft includes some $ 44.8 billion in tax cuts. Corporate and personal income tax rates as well as inheritance levies will be cut in the new tax plan, which <ORGANIZATION> LDP </ORGANIZATION> officials say they hope to implement by April 1989. `` It took six months for us only to agree on the sales tax rate,'' said <PERSON> Sadanori </PERSON> <PERSON> Yamanaka </PERSON>, the legislator who heads the council. `` Now, the party must be firmly united under the new plan to overcome the opposition parties' attempt to block the bill.'' The new tax plan caps long and fiercely-debated sessions regarding the amount of tax reductions and the level of sales taxes among ruling party members and finance ministry officials. But it also is expected to come under hot debate from opposition parties in the upcoming session of the Diet, the Japanese parliament. The new plan finalized Tuesday marks the third attempt by the government and ruling party to introduce an indirect tax, following others in 1979 and 1987. Last year, then-Prime Minister <PERSON> Yasuhiro </PERSON> <PERSON> Nakasone </PERSON> suffered a serious political setback when his party was defeated in local elections over the sales tax issue. <PERSON> Shintaro </PERSON> <PERSON> Abe </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> LDP </ORGANIZATION> secretary general, said after unveiling the new tax plan that the party still faced the task of garnering wide support for the reform package. `` We have just completed the first stage,'' he said. `` The next steps are going to be the real challenge, but I think there is a consensus within the party.'' Opposition party leaders denounced the ruling party's decision to push forward with the once-defeated tax reform plan. `` It is a serious challenge to the people of our country,'' said <PERSON> Shizuo </PERSON> <PERSON> Yamaguchi </PERSON>, secretary general of the <ORGANIZATION> Japan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Socialist </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION>, the largest opposition party. `` The <ORGANIZATION> LDP </ORGANIZATION> must dissolve the Diet and let the people decide on the issue.'' <PERSON> Satsuki </PERSON> <PERSON> Eda </PERSON>, chairman of the <ORGANIZATION> Social </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Democratic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Alliance </ORGANIZATION>, said, `` I am determined to cooperate with other opposition parties to block the passage of the new tax law in the Diet by all means.'' The <ORGANIZATION> Finance </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ministry </ORGANIZATION> _ which had sought a 5 percent sales tax _ also welcomed the new tax system as a boost to the domestic economy. `` The new tax system is expected to lift the gross national product by 0.1 percent,'' said a <ORGANIZATION> Finance </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ministry </ORGANIZATION> official. As a result, `` the Japanese economy will be vitalized and expanded domestic demand will draw more imports.'' <ORGANIZATION> Finance </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ministry </ORGANIZATION> officials have argued that revenue from a 3 percent sales tax would total only about $ 40 billion to $ 43 billion, short of the amount slated in tax cuts. The ministry has said it hopes to eliminate budget deficit-covering bond issues by fiscal 1990, but may have to revise its target if the new <ORGANIZATION> LDP </ORGANIZATION> plan is passed. An <ORGANIZATION> LDP </ORGANIZATION> official said the tax plan will be presented to the Diet in July for passage by next fall.
